schools.name: Donald B. Dixon-Lyle R. Smith Middle School

data.description: Fantastic chance to own a home in a welcoming, long-established neighborhood just moments from downtown Fredericksburg! This residence is a gem, boasting plenty of charm and history as a classic colonial from 1933. Nestled on a corner lot, the side yard is fully fenced and framed by beautiful, mature trees like Magnolia, Holly, Dogwood, Maple, and Oak. This property invites exploration with its thoughtfully landscaped perennial gardens that bloom throughout the seasons.  Step onto the sizable covered front porch and take in the surroundings. Inside, discover hardwood floors, an elegant brick fireplace, beautiful wood detailing, and built-in features showcasing craftsmanship rarely found in modern homes.  The kitchen has granite countertops and overlooks a fenced side yard with a raised garden bed crafted with curved stacked slate. The main level has various living spaces—a living room, dining area, office, and a full bath, along with a convenient mudroom leading to a partially shaded large deck.  The backyard offers a wooden shingled carport, a brick driveway, and two storage sheds for all your outdoor storage needs. Upstairs, three bedrooms and a spacious full bath await, while the finished third level provides flexibility as a bonus room or fourth bedroom.  The partially finished basement, with a separate exit, doubles as a recreation room and houses the washer and dryer closet, along with a utility sink in the unfinished section.   For qualified buyers, there's potential for a $17,500 grant with a preferred lender. Don't miss out on the opportunity to experience this unique home—Call to book a private showing today!
